tags.description: Blackhawk Park, originally referred to as Kingsport Villages Park, is an 8-acre park on the west side of town.  Three acres of this is a pond stocked with some of the best fish in town. The pond is restocked in the spring and fall.
tags.name: Blackhawk Park
tags.note:

tags.description: Once the site of Lincoln School, this 2.5-acre park site adjoins the Elgin National Watch Co.'s observatory. A small playground is located on this parcel. In 2013 a gazebo shelter was constructed as a result of the leadership provided by the Kiwanis Club
tags.name: Kiwanis Park

tags.description: Walton Island, located just south of the Elgin Dam on the Fox River in downtown Elgin was created in the WPA program of the 1930's. It was dedicated to the City by the Izaak Walton League.
